quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,109,"Indeed, there was a party of My servants who said, 'Our Lord, we have believed, so forgive us and have mercy upon us, and You are the best of the merciful.'"
  23,110,"But you took them in mockery to the point that they made you forget My remembrance, and you used to laugh at them."
  23,111,"Indeed, I have rewarded them this Day for their patient endurance - that they are the attainers [of success]."
  25,55,"But they worship rather than Allāh that which does not benefit them or harm them, and the disbeliever is ever, against his Lord, an assistant [to Satan]."
  25,56,"And We have not sent you, [O Muḥammad], except as a bringer of good tidings and a warner."
  25,57,"Say, "
  26,28,"[Moses] said, "
  26,29,"[Pharaoh] said, "
  26,30,"[Moses] said, "
  27,1,"Ṭā, Seen.{1} These are the verses of the Qur’ān [i.e., recitation] and a clear Book",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  27,2,"As guidance and good tidings for the believers"
  27,3,"Who establish prayer and give zakāh, and of the Hereafter they are certain [in faith]."